suites.name: Validation of the successful borrowing estimate calcualation functionality

tests.name: I launch the borrowing calculator webApp
I should the page title as "Home loan borrowing power calculator | ANZ"
I click on the "Single" radio buton of Application type field
I select 0 from the Number of dependants drop down
I click on the "Home to live in" Property you would like to buy radio button
I enter "80,000" on the text box "Your income (before tax)"
I enter "10,000" on the text box "Your other income"
I enter "500" on the text box "Living expenses"
I enter "0" on the text box "Current home loan repayments"
I enter "100" on the text box "Other loan repayments"
I enter "0" on the text box "Other commitments"
I enter "10,000" on the text box "Total credit card limits"
I click on the "Work out how much I could borrow" button
I should see the We estimate you could borrow field with "$479,000" value

suites.name: Validation of startover functionality which clears all relevent fields

tests.name: I launch the borrowing calculator webApp
I should the page title as "Home loan borrowing power calculator | ANZ"

suites.name: Validation for warning message to contact the customer care

tests.name: I launch the borrowing calculator webApp
I should the page title as "Home loan borrowing power calculator | ANZ"
I enter "1" on the text box "Living expenses"
I click on the "Work out how much I could borrow" button
I should see error message "Based on the details you've entered, we're unable to give you an estimate of your borrowing power with this calculator. For questions, call us on 1800 100 641."
